NOTES ON AES & VDI DOC

1.  There is a known bug in the drop-down menu-handling of the Retail GEM
AES v1.1.  The symptoms are that you sometimes have to move into the
menu area twice in order to get the drop-down menu to be displayed.
These symptoms are most noticeable when your application is waiting for
single clicks in its main event_multi().  The work-around is to wait for
double clicks even if your application doesn't care about double clicks.
The problem is still there even with double click waiting, but it turns
into a race condition that won't happen very often in real use.  The
problem was  fixed completely in Version 1.2 GEM AES, but you will
want to use the work-around so that you can work on the copies of 
GEM that have already been sold.

2.  The sample Assembly Language Program included in the VDI Programmer's
Guide (page 2-3) does not work properly. 

3.  In the VDI manual, Inquire Text Extent (page 8-15) where control(3) is
described, change "number of words in text" to "number of characters in text".
 
4.  In the VDI manual, Inquire Cell Array (pages 8-23, 8-24) change Output 
Arguments (8-24) from colarray[n] = intin[n] to colorray[n] = intout[n].

5.  In the AES manual where AC_OPEN is described, it should say word 0 = 40.

6.   In the AES manual where AC_CLOSE is described, it should say word 0 = 41.

7.  In the FORM LIBRARY under form_do, where fo_dostartob is described, change
the application "can pass in a value of -1" to "can pass in a value of 0".

8.  Passing a handle of 0 to any VDI function may result in unpredictable 
results.  Workaround:  NEVER PASS A HANDLE OF 0 TO ANY VDI CALL.

9.  There is no checking performed to assure that your menus are no larger 
than 1/4 of your screen size.  If you do create a menu larger than 1/4 screen 
size you will overwrite memory causing unpredictable results.

